       RowBox[{"Cos", "[", "\[Theta]", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], ";", "\n", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(*", 
     RowBox[{"confirm", " ", "identity"}], "*)"}], "\n", " ", 
    RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", "\n", "  ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Tr", "[", 
        RowBox[{"n", " ", ".", " ", "\[Sigma]", " ", ".", " ", "\[Rho]"}], 
        "]"}], " ", "==", " ", "\n", "   ", 
       RowBox[{"n", " ", ".", " ", "blochvector"}]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
         "r", " ", "|", " ", "\[Theta]r", " ", "|", " ", "\[Phi]r", " ", "|", 
          " ", "\[Theta]", " ", "|", " ", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}], " ", "\\\n"}], "\[Element]",
        " ", "Reals"}]}], "]"}]}]}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[212]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"61c1cfd1-b972-4d8a-9b31-f1280a213eb4"],

Cell["Beyond Projective Measurements: POVMs", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"316f4c1e-7317-4612-9eba-a1c2dd70cdbe"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Recall for spin-measurement along a unit vector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  OverscriptBox[
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[RightVector]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ad31c969-da78-4760-b60c-c64e921ff04f"],
 ", the corresponding projectors are given by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\|01d4ab", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"]},
      "Ket"], 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"]},
      "Bra"]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       SpanMaxSize->1], 
      RowBox[{"\|01d540", "\[PlusMinus]", 
       RowBox[{
        OverscriptBox[
         StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[RightVector]"], ".", 
        OverscriptBox[
         StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "\[RightVector]"]}]}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       SpanMaxSize->1]}]}]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fbdb4f24-bb51-4752-a3f7-0d6c5aa67271"],
 " and probabilities are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["p", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\|01d4ab", 
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"]], 
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "72b2747b-e495-4cc8-a64d-e501af1aac3b"],
 ". These measurement scenarios are usually called PVM (projective-valued \
measure): you pick an orthonormal basis ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["n", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"]},
    "Ket"], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "508a5058-fb88-46d1-ac4a-34b12f792028"],
 " and the outcomes correspond to orthogonal projectors. That\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s great, but it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s not general enough for \
what real experiments and real information-theory tasks demand. In many \
situations we also want measurements that extract only partial information \
(so-called unsharp or weak measurements) because we want to trade information \
gain for reduced disturbance, or because we are continuously monitoring a \
system."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a6c38f65-b6d5-449b-aabc-e78ef9e9ac28"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s focus on a specific unsharp measurement. An \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]unsharp Pauli-X\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] measurement is \
what you get when you want to ask the qubit a X-question, \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]are you more like ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["x", "TI"], "+"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8e922776-f65f-482b-bf13-062a48735f16"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["x", "TI"], "-"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7608f1a7-cb78-4599-aa22-4652869dd1b2"],
 "?\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], but you don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t want to force a \
fully projective collapse, or your apparatus simply can\[CloseCurlyQuote]t \
resolve X perfectly. Instead of returning a crisp yes/no that perfectly \
separates ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["x", "TI"], "+"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a8ec6ebf-2c3f-481d-8edb-8974b13e4b76"],
 " from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["x", "TI"], "-"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "be7c7292-7c3a-4378-9878-d7b34b229adf"],
 ", the device returns a noisy answer: it is biased toward \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]+\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] when the qubit has positive \
X-polarization and biased toward \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]\[Minus]\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] when it has negative X-polarization, but the bias is \
smaller than a sharp measurement would give. Operationally, it\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s like measuring X and then flipping the classical outcome \
with some probability, or like coupling weakly to the qubit so you only \
extract partial X-information."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"36e88403-41f6-40ba-8548-015e49a5b309"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Mathematically, the above scenario can be described by by two effects: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "+"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "498dfe09-7361-4830-92ac-522aa1d14212"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "-"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a7a5355c-d205-4a2c-adc5-aba0e502de5f"],
 " where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "\[PlusMinus]"], "=", "1", "/", "2", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"\|01d540", "\[PlusMinus]", 
    StyleBox["\[Eta]", "TI"], " ", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["x", "TI"]]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "91ff5710-ffd8-4d44-8d97-a307019dcd1e"],
 " with \[Eta] the sharpness (or measurement strength). The set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "+"]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "-"], "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "54bc4758-ad9e-42e7-a3cf-d8d8db9765dc"],
 " is usually called POVM for \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Positive Operator-Valued \
Measure\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] (sometimes also written \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Probability Operator-Valued Measure\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote])."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"76691ddf-aa56-44a7-ae94-36076fa3befa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Show the matrix form of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "\[PlusMinus]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ed0e898e-ca1a-4663-bad0-fa086517183d"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"557e7b60-45ea-4a74-8532-3a06c8394fa6"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "\[Eta]", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalE]", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], " ", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}], " ", "+", " ", 
        RowBox[{"\[Eta]", " ", 
         RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "1", "]"}]}]}], ")"}]}], ",", " ", "\n", 
     "   ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], " ", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}], " ", "-", " ", 
        RowBox[{"\[Eta]", " ", 
         RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "1", "]"}]}]}], ")"}]}]}], "}"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"AssociationThread", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(\[ScriptCapitalE]\\), \\(+\\)]\\)\>\
\"", ",", 
     " ", "\"\<\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(\[ScriptCapitalE]\\), \
\\(-\\)]\\)\>\""}], "}"}], ",", " ", "\n", " ", 
   RowBox[{"MatrixForm", " ", "/@", " ", "\[ScriptCapitalE]"}]}], 
  "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[213]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"d6c415ce-4f63-4d57-8a0a-bc70d7f0a129"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "\[PlusMinus]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "63844390-3a2c-44d6-bd06-6dd128b94c99"],
 " are positive semi-definite (eigenvalues equal or larger than zero):"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"23fb3d22-4e77-462a-bdcf-00fe2c02bd9a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"#", " ", ">=", " ", "0"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"0", " ", "<=", " ", "\[Eta]", " ", "<=", " ", "1"}]}], "]"}], 
     " ", "&"}], "]"}], "@*", "\n", "  ", "Eigenvalues"}], " ", "/@", " ", 
  "\[ScriptCapitalE]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[214]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"8be27b50-b808-436d-91e4-5b26e29932d3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "\[PlusMinus]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "781f8205-a8eb-4e4c-bcd7-660665abd258"],
 " are Hermitian:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4dcfd1ef-2244-454b-b795-3a7f9fc418e4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"#", " ", "==", " ", 
      RowBox[{"ConjugateTranspose", "[", "#", "]"}]}], ",", " ", "\n", "   ", 
     
     RowBox[{"0", " ", "<=", " ", "\[Eta]", " ", "<=", " ", "1"}]}], "]"}], 
   " ", "&"}], " ", "/@", " ", "\[ScriptCapitalE]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[215]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"2d3f7dae-121a-4feb-8abc-c38fef382c31"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "+"], "+", 
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "-"], "=", "\|01d540"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "44a0fe30-527b-4685-8c62-ab68621eb679"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e5392eea-c06c-44c4-8bfb-7fab90eec63a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Total", "[", "\[ScriptCapitalE]", "]"}], " ", "==", " ", 
   RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "FullSimplify"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[216]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"e2819e88-e91c-439d-81d1-d388fe88ce3c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Using Born rule for POVMs one gets ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["p", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["k", "TI"]], "=", 
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", 
     StyleBox["k", "TI"]], 
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "42016f79-5497-4788-9275-75577650c087"],
 ". Writing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], "=", "1", "/", "2", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\|01d540", "+", 
     OverscriptBox[
      StyleBox["r", "TI"], "\[RightVector]"]}], ".", 
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], "\[RightVector]"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c36402cb-e5da-45cc-8b64-c4c6e87d36e2"],
 " one finds that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["p", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"], "=", "1", "/", "2", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"1", "\[PlusMinus]", 
    StyleBox["\[Eta]", "TI"], " ", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["x", "TI"]]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "78afe880-4971-4f24-bb8f-195249711554"],
 " where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["x", "TI"]], "=", 
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["x", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e974000f-02d1-4183-9728-2275c7b2af27"],
 ". So unsharp X measurement only \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]sees\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] the x-component of the Bloch vector, scaled by \
\[Eta]."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"88b30a05-7e28-4830-bb4c-d16931e5bac0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["p", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]"], "=", "1", "/", "2", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"1", "\[PlusMinus]", 
    StyleBox["\[Eta]", "TI"], " ", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["x", "TI"]]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "744dde71-b496-4c2a-a737-30ac8758a0a8"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"75d9b567-8a9e-405f-9a0e-50086c27fff7"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", 
  RowBox[{"rx", ",", " ", "ry", ",", " ", "rz"}], "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"FullSimplify", " ", "/@", " ", "\n", " ", 
  RowBox[{"AssociationThread", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(p\\), \\(+\\)]\\)\>\"", ",", " ", 
      "\n", "   ", "\"\<\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(p\\), \\(-\\)]\\)\>\""}], 
     "}"}], ",", " ", "\n", "  ", 
    RowBox[{"With", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"r", " ", "=", " ", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"rx", ",", " ", "ry", ",", " ", "rz"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
      " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"\[Rho]", " ", "=", " ", 
        RowBox[{"DensityMatrix", "[", "r", "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", "\n", 
      "   ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Tr", "[", 
         RowBox[{"#", " ", ".", " ", "\[Rho]"}], "]"}], " ", "&"}], " ", "/@",
        " ", "\[ScriptCapitalE]"}]}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[217]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"f0c8ceaa-2a85-43fb-9fef-921f8cc4905f"],

Cell["POVMs: Post-Measurement States", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"8903fedd-51f2-4ba5-9dca-5fd27c74b519"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "As you may recall, for projective measurement, the post-measurement state \
was the eigenstate corresponding to the observed eigenvalue. In other words, \
the state collapses into one of the eigenstates of the observable. For POVMs, \
the effects ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "\[PlusMinus]"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "caedd4f1-a12e-4459-b72f-a387004fc007"],
 " fix the statistics. But the post-measurement state depends on how you \
implement the measurement physically. A set of operators ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "eb4e07cc-6ca1-4959-adbe-3e42ddef476f"],
 " (Kraus/measurement operators) defines how the state updates conditioned on \
outcome ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1aac41a5-2432-4d0e-bb75-675bc5aec654"],
 ": the probability is given by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["p", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["j", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
     StyleBox["j", "TI"]], 
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], " ", 
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
     StyleBox["j", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6ddb32f3-012d-48b8-8461-1d6a62b1f1f8"],
 " where the post-measurement state is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "=", 
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], " ", 
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], "/", 
   StyleBox["p", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["j", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "76f439e9-1ee2-488f-856f-88e66c4cd17c"],
 ". So the associated effect is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "=", 
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], 
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "29846982-4177-43d6-bd44-86e99c6eb33c"],
 ". This guarantees that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", 
   StyleBox["j", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "52a8fb24-0a8b-4fbd-9eb3-617f8dc96bd4"],
 " is positive semidefinite and also ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"],
    LimitsPositioning->False], 
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "=", "\|01d540"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e9144255-699d-4045-b95b-12399a5f5750"],
 " corresponds to overall probability 1. The equation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "=", 
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], 
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7e646088-5c30-4871-8b0a-6852f1d0a5d1"],
 " means that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
   StyleBox["j", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "65d0e1b9-ebb4-4fc5-9993-e577ec967cf4"],
 " is an \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]amplitude-level\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
description of producing outcome ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "52fed931-d750-47e5-88a2-8b1e32998bf0"],
 ": squaring it (in the matrix/operator sense) gives the effect that \
determines probabilities. But many different physical procedures can produce \
the same probabilities, which is why ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
   StyleBox["j", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a8a1a1d9-ccd2-4eb8-b935-1a86c631aeab"],
 " is not unique even when ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", 
   StyleBox["j", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f4d00cf2-928f-41a7-a3b6-36df3aaa0ecb"],
 "\:200b is fixed."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8d666755-e250-4602-8fc1-1b4b7c96445f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The first and most direct way to choose ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
   StyleBox["j", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d74997a0-8ae7-4f2a-97ae-4f1920b8cd6c"],
 " for unsharp measurements is the square-root, often called \
L\[UDoubleDot]ders-type instrument: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", 
    StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "=", 
   SqrtBox[
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", 
     StyleBox["j", "TI"]]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "88d575b8-80b4-4d36-ac9f-4e0447760ed3"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"933c6d08-9734-4c0b-9e3c-415481422bda"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Find ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalM]", "\[PlusMinus]"], "=", 
   SqrtBox[
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", "\[PlusMinus]"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
